message.content: Based on the provided volatility data, a possible payload of the initial exploit affecting the victim's bank account could be the file "sdra64.exe" located in \Device\HarddiskVolume1\WINDOWS\system32\. This file stands out as it is not a standard Windows system file and could potentially be a malicious executable that was part of the exploit. Further analysis of this file, its behavior, and any associated network activity would be necessary to confirm its role in the suspected malicious activity impacting the victim's bank account.
